  {
   "name": "Benefit Rights and Information",
   "elements": [
    {
     "type": "html",
     "name": "BRI Info",
     "html": "<b>Attention:</b><br>\nYou must read the following Benefit Rights Information. You have a legal responsibility to know and follow all rules and requirements of the UI program. If you have a question about your responsibilities or the requirements of receiving benefits, the UI customer service is here to help. Please contact 1-866-239-0843. \n<br><br>\n<b>Unemployment Insurance Handbook</b><br>\nThe UI Handbook will answer most questions about your UI claim and help you avoid problems, delays, and improper payments. It explains your rights and responsibilities while claiming UI benefits.  You are responsible for reading and knowing the contents of this handbook.\n<br><br>\nAccess the Unemployment Insurance Handbook by clicking <a href=\"https://www.iowaworkforcedevelopment.gov/unemployment-insurance-benefits-handbook-guide-unemployment-insurance-benefits\">here:</a>\n<br><br>\n<b>Monetary Eligibility</b><br>\nWe will send you a monetary record, if this is the first application you have filed in the past 12 months or more. Even though your Monetary Record may show UI benefit amounts, you must meet additional requirements to receive UI benefits.\n<br><br>\nReview the record carefully to make sure the information is accurate.  Contact us immediately if any information is incorrect. Wages you earned in other states, from military or federal employer will not be listed on your first monetary record because these wages must be requested. Once we receive your wages, we will send you a corrected monetary record.\n<br><br>\nThe Monetary Record shows the following:\n<ul>\n<li>Start date of the claim</li>\n<li>Number of dependents claimed</li>\n<li>Work search requirements</li>\n<li>Weekly Benefit Amount (WBA)</li>\n<li>Maximum Benefit Amount (MBA)</li>\n<li>Employers you worked for during the base period and the last employer</li>\n<li>Wages you earned each quarter</li>\n</ul>\n<b>Requesting a UI Benefit Payment</b><br>\nTo request a UI benefit payment, you must file a weekly claim. You may submit your first weekly claim on <<basePeriodBeginDate>>\n<br><br>\nYou will be reporting information for the week of <<effectiveDate>> through <<saturdayAfterEffectiveDate>>.\n<br><br>\nYou can file your weekly claim online through your Claimant Portal.\n<br><br>\n<b>You will be asked to report if you</b>\n<ul>\n<li>Are totally or partially unemployed</li>\n<li>Are able and available for work</li>\n<li>Have refused any job offers or referrals</li>\n<li>Are actively looking for work (unless waived)</li>\n<li>Work search information (date applied for the job, position applied for, company contact information, etc.)</li>\n<li>Have or will receive earnings, vacation pay, holiday pay, severance pay</li>\n<li>Have or will receive pension and workers’ compensation</li>\n</ul>"
    }
   ],
   "title": "Benefit Rights and Information",
   "category": "Benefit Rights and Information"
  }
